The Human Side of Protection • “I can remember the first day of my first international tour. I’d been in the business a while by then, but the scale was a whole other level. There were so many people, and everyone had a job to do.  One thing I noticed is that, from my vantage point, everyone seemed to be the best at what they did.  From the choreographer to the lighting director, everyone showed a high level of mastery of their work.  Whenever you are in a new environment, you can feel a bit like a fish out of water, and I felt that uncertainty. Some call it imposters syndrome, which is all in your head, as I knew I had the talents.  I also remember it was then where I recommitted to being the best representation of my industry that I could be.” • The ICON Advanced Executive Protection Course,  March 20-March 29, 2023. @iconglobalep #ExecutiveProtection #Bodyguards #Bodyguard #training #MasterClass #ICON

It’s good to have goals no matter what stage you are in career wise - For example, while I’ve done many different speaking engagements over the years, I’m very honored to have just completed my first international talk.  Believe it or not, public speaking doesn’t come naturally to me, now add to the fact that I’m speaking at the largest security conference in Latin America where the the overwhelming majority of the room are Spanish speakers, and the pressure intensified.  Oh, did I mention that right before me was the Minister Counselor for Diplomatic Security with the US Embassy? Pressure intensified.  My solution? Exhale, trust my knowledge of the subject matter, and just talk with the intent of sharing, not impressing.  Many thanks to the organizers of the @epsummit, @pmonasterio, @combatmf & @ivan_ivanovich.ms. Honorable mention to the translation team which was working round the clock with amazing results, and @jlasorsa3 & @officialchrisstory for the lessons learned from Day 1 of the event.  Work. Learn. Absorb. Repeat.  #ExecutiveeProtection #Bodyguard #Masterclass #PressurebutNoPressure #ICON

The Business of Protection 

Through the years of all the programs and sessions that Elijah and I have taught together, the sessions I love the most is when we focus on the business of protection.

Anyone can teach you how to walk in formation and respond to an attack on principal, but few can teach you how to differentiate yourself.  How to find work and build a sustainable business model.  But most importantly how to calibrate the passion and the hunger with the patience, so it is built to last!
